{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionLLM stands for Large Language Model, an artificial intelligence model capable of understanding and generating human-like text.",
    "These models are trained on vast amounts of text data and can perform tasks such as text generation, text summarization, machine translation, and questionanswering [32].",
    "LLMs have various applications across industries including, natural language processing (NLP), chatbots, content generation, and sentiment analysis [18].",
    "They are crucial in advancing AI technology and revolutionizing human-computer interactions [11].",
    "LLMs utilize a transformer architecture model, serving as a foundation for generative AI applications, along with generative adversarial networks (GANs) [26] and variational autoencoders (VAEs) [30].Several researchers focus on reviewing the literature on generative AI and LLM technology in various application domains."
  ],
